a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes z :: complex
assumes h0 : "z = Complex (5/6) 2"
shows  "cmod z = 13 / 6"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Evaluate $\left|\frac56 +2i\right|$. The final Answer is \frac{13}{6}
 ### Proof
 We have \[\left|\frac56 +2i\right| = \left|\frac{1}{6}\left(5 +12i\right)\right| = \frac16|5+12i| = \frac16\sqrt{5^2 +12^2} = \boxed{\frac{13}{6}}.\]
 *)

theorem
fixes z :: complex
assumes h0 : "z = Complex (5/6) 2"
shows  "cmod z = 13 / 6"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Find the absolute value (or modulus) of the complex number $(5/6) + 2i$. The final answer is $13/6$.
